{"id": "f001", "text": "The cosmological argument holds that contingent beings require a necessary being as their ground.", "split": "train", "title": "Summa", "author": "Thomas Aquinas", "year": 1274, "language": "en", "religion": "christian", "tradition": "christian", "school": "scholastic", "topic": ["existence_of_god"], "stance": "argues_for", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "aquinas_summa_god", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 20}
{"id": "f002", "text": "Evil and omnipotence are logically incompatible; no free will defence removes natural suffering.", "split": "train", "title": "Evil and Omnipotence", "author": "J. L. Mackie", "year": 1955, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "atheism", "school": "analytic_philosophy", "topic": ["problem_of_evil", "existence_of_god"], "stance": "argues_against", "source_type": "essay", "source_id": "mackie_evil_1955", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 18}
{"id": "f003", "text": "Form is not-self; if form were self it would not lead to affliction.", "split": "train", "title": "Anattā Sutta", "author": "Buddha", "year": -500, "language": "en", "religion": "buddhist", "tradition": "buddhist", "school": "theravada", "topic": ["no_self", "soul"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "scripture", "source_id": "sutta_anatta", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 15}
{"id": "f004", "text": "Joshu said: Mu! The gateless gate cannot be entered by conceptual reasoning alone. No fixed self can pass through.", "split": "train", "title": "Mumonkan", "author": "Mumon", "year": 1228, "language": "en", "religion": "buddhist", "tradition": "buddhist", "school": "zen", "topic": ["logic", "meaning", "no_self"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "mumonkan", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 16}
{"id": "f005", "text": "All phenomena are empty of inherent existence; dependent origination is the middle way. No self abides.", "split": "train", "title": "Mūlamadhyamakakārikā", "author": "Nāgārjuna", "year": 200, "language": "en", "religion": "buddhist", "tradition": "buddhist", "school": "tibetan", "topic": ["emptiness", "existence_of_god", "no_self"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "nagarjuna_madhyamaka", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 17}
{"id": "f006", "text": "What does existence mean? Both theist and atheist debate without examining ontology.", "split": "train", "title": "Debate Critique Q&A", "author": "Acharya Prashant", "year": 2025, "language": "en", "original_language": "hi", "religion": "hindu", "tradition": "hindu", "school": "advaita", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "non_duality"], "stance": "argues_against", "source_type": "dialogue_qa", "source_id": "prashant_debate_critique", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 16}
{"id": "f007", "text": "God is dead as a dogma; Zen points beyond belief and disbelief.", "split": "train", "title": "God Is Dead", "author": "Osho", "year": 1990, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "critique_of_religion", "school": "zen", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "critique_of_religion"], "stance": "argues_against", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "osho_god_is_dead", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 14}
{"id": "f008", "text": "In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.", "split": "train", "title": "Bible (KJV)", "author": "Various", "year": 1769, "language": "en", "religion": "christian", "tradition": "christian", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "revelation"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "scripture", "source_id": "bible_kjv", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 12}
{"id": "f009", "text": "All praise is due to Allah, Lord of the worlds, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful.", "split": "train", "title": "Qur'an (Rodwell)", "author": "Muhammad", "year": 1861, "language": "en", "religion": "islam", "tradition": "islamic", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "devotion"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "scripture", "source_id": "quran_rodwell", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 16}
{"id": "f010", "text": "The soul is never born nor does it die; it is eternal and indestructible.", "split": "train", "title": "Bhagavad Gita", "author": "Vyasa", "year": 2023, "language": "en", "religion": "hindu", "tradition": "hindu", "school": "dvaita", "topic": ["soul", "existence_of_god"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "scripture", "source_id": "gita_ttd_2023", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 15}
{"id": "f011", "text": "One Universal Creator God; truth is the name, creative being personified.", "split": "train", "title": "Guru Granth Sahib", "author": "Guru Nanak", "year": 2020, "language": "en", "religion": "sikh", "tradition": "sikh", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "devotion"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "scripture", "source_id": "ggs_sant_singh_khalsa", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 14}
{"id": "f012", "text": "I refuse to accept any creed based on blind faith; reason is my guide.", "split": "train", "title": "Why I Am an Atheist", "author": "Bhagat Singh", "year": 1930, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "atheism", "school": "indian_secularism", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "faith_vs_evidence"], "stance": "argues_against", "source_type": "essay", "source_id": "bhagat_singh_wiaa", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 15}
{"id": "f013", "text": "The hierarchical causal argument suggests sustaining causes cannot regress infinitely.", "split": "train", "title": "Big Think Interview", "author": "Alex O'Connor", "year": 2024, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "atheism", "school": "analytic_philosophy", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "nihilism"], "stance": "survey", "source_type": "interview", "source_id": "oconnor_bigthink", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 14}
{"id": "f014", "text": "Science cannot be the standard for proving a non-physical God; logic must decide.", "split": "train", "title": "Does God Exist?", "author": "Mufti Shamail Nadwi", "year": 2024, "language": "en", "religion": "islam", "tradition": "islamic", "school": "islamic_philosophy", "topic": ["existence_of_god", "faith_vs_evidence"], "stance": "argues_for", "source_type": "debate_transcript", "source_id": "debate_akhtar_nadwi", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 16}
{"id": "f015", "text": "Free will defence shows God cannot create significantly free creatures who never choose evil.", "split": "train", "title": "God, Freedom, and Evil", "author": "Alvin Plantinga", "year": 1974, "language": "en", "religion": "christian", "tradition": "christian", "school": "analytic_philosophy", "topic": ["problem_of_evil", "free_will"], "stance": "argues_for", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "plantinga_gfe", "license": "licensed", "token_count": 16}
{"id": "f016", "text": "Premise: God exists because design is obvious. Fallacy: argument from ignorance.", "split": "train", "title": "LOGOS Fallacy Corpus", "author": "LOGOS", "year": 2026, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "logic", "school": "logic", "topic": ["fallacy", "logic"], "stance": "survey", "source_type": "essay", "source_id": "logos_fallacies", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 14}
{"id": "f017", "text": "Bias: confirmation bias. Example: counting answered prayers only. Remedy: track misses.", "split": "train", "title": "LOGOS Bias Corpus", "author": "LOGOS", "year": 2026, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "moral_psychology", "school": "moral_psychology", "topic": ["epistemology"], "stance": "survey", "source_type": "essay", "source_id": "logos_biases", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 13}
{"id": "f018", "text": "Anekāntavāda teaches that reality is many-sided; no single view exhausts truth.", "split": "train", "title": "Tattvārtha Sūtra", "author": "Umasvati", "year": 200, "language": "en", "religion": "jain", "tradition": "jain", "school": "jain", "topic": ["epistemology"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "jain_tattvartha", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 15}
{"id": "f019", "text": "Holdout scripture span reserved for evaluation only.", "split": "holdout", "title": "Bible (KJV)", "author": "Various", "year": 1769, "language": "en", "religion": "christian", "tradition": "christian", "topic": ["meaning"], "stance": "primary_source", "source_type": "scripture", "source_id": "bible_kjv", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 10}
{"id": "f020", "text": "The greatest happiness principle grounds morality in consequences for all affected.", "split": "train", "title": "Utilitarianism", "author": "John Stuart Mill", "year": 1863, "language": "en", "religion": "none", "tradition": "secular_humanism", "school": "utilitarian", "topic": ["utilitarianism", "morality"], "stance": "argues_for", "source_type": "book", "source_id": "mill_utilitarianism_1863", "license": "PD-US", "token_count": 14}
